  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThere are several instances of manual `let else` usage within the Lighthouse codebase. Clippy has a lint that warns on manual `let else` usage when the `match` has only one other arm: https://rust-lang.github.io/rust-clippy/master/index.html#/manual_let_else\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to add this lint and refactor accordingly as it can improve code readability & aligns w/ idiomatic usage of Rust\r\n\r\n## Example\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/441fc1691b69f9edc4bbdc6665f3efab16265c9b/beacon_node/http_api/src/sync_committees.rs#L33-L38\r\n\r\ncan be refactored to\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nlet Some(altair_fork_epoch) = chain.spec.altair_fork_epoch else {\r\n  // Empty response for networks with Altair disabled.\r\n  return Ok(convert_to_response(vec![], false));\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nEnable `clippy::manual_let_else` lint and resolve the warning messages.\r\n",
